---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';
import ericSarahDawn from '~/assets/images/eric_sarah_dawn.avif';
import liningUp from '~/assets/images/lining_up.avif';

const metadata = {
  title: 'About',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata} accentColor="blue">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <Hero tagline="About MojoKickball">
    <Fragment slot="title">
      Inclusion with <span class="text-accent">Contribution</span>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      MojoKickball was created to change "sports-ball" to be something that allows meaningful contributions from a larger pool of players. 
      Many recreational sports leagues still end up dominated by the same competitive players, leaving everyone else to watch from the sidelines. Mojo is different by design.
    </Fragment>
  </Hero>

  <!-- Origin Story -->
  <Content
    isReversed
    tagline="The Story"
    title="Why we need this"
    items={[
      {
        title: 'A problem with traditional sports',
        description:
          'Traditional sports often have higher barriers to entry. Many traditional sports were designed around one or two highly specific abilities. e.g. throw hard, run fast, be agile, etc. The "fun" gets concentrated amongst the most athletic and the most competitive.',
      },
      {
        title: 'A sport designed for everyone',
        description:
          'By combining kickball, tag, dodgeball, hot potato, keep-away (and maybe a few other activities), the game creates multiple roles and entry-points — a wider range of abilities can meaningfully contribute.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Kindness, cleverness and honor',
        description: 'Engendering agency in your fellow teammates isn\'t just kind - it\'s vital. Learning everyone\'s names isn\'t just about being nice - it\'s a super-power.' 
      },
      {
        title: 'The fun of agency',
        description:
          'The game flips a lot of tropes on their head. It is a game where not catching a ball, not running too quickly, or not making it around the bases can be just as strategic as catching well, running fast, or scoring a point.',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: ericSarahDawn,
      alt: 'Eric with MojoKickball players',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      MojoKickball was invented in Austin, Texas in 2006. The creator, Eric Heiberg brought it to Minneapolis in 2013, 
      where it's been running every summer since. New players are always welcome.
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Philosophy -->
  <Content
    isAfterContent
    tagline="The Philosophy"
    title="Inclusion with Contribution"
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Everyone has a role',
        description:
          'Pitchers, runners, fielders, and chasers all play differently. The game creates multiple pathways to contribute. Nobody is standing around.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Low contact, high fun',
        description:
          'Lightweight balls and rules that emphasize strategy over strength keep the game accessible to everyone from age 10 and up.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Community first',
        description:
          'Mojo is free to play. A $5 suggested donation helps cover field rental and equipment — but the door is always open regardless.',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: liningUp,
      alt: 'MojoKickball players lining up at Kenwood Park',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      Inclusion with contribution is about imbuing players with agency - the idea that you can radically change the outcome 
      of a game in a positive and meaningful way, just the way you are. 
    </Fragment> 
  </Content>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <CallToAction
    actions={[
      {
        variant: 'primary',
        text: 'Contact us',
        href: '/contact',
      },
    ]}
  >
    <Fragment slot="title">Questions? Want to start your own Mojo league?</Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      Resources are available if you want to bring 6-ball kickball to your city. Reach out and we will help you get started.
    </Fragment>
  </CallToAction>
</Layout>
